\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. A. andrachne} L.,{\i  Syst. Nat.} ed. 10,{\b  2}: 1024 (1759). Like {\b 1} but bark smooth, peeling off in papery sheets, orange-red; young twigs glabrous; leaves 3-6 cm wide, less than twice as long as wide, often entire; petiole 15-30 mm; panicle erect, appearing in spring; calyx 2·5 mm, with ovate-rhombic, acute lobes; berry 8-12 mm, reticulate-sulcate, orange.{\i  Evergreen scrub and rocky slopes. S. Albania, Greece, Aegean region; S. Krym.} Al Cr Gr Rs (K) Tu.
