\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  A.} × {\b andrachnoides} Link, {\i Enum. Hort. Berol. Alt.}{\b  1}: 395 (1821), the hybrid between {\b 1} and {\b 2}, is frequent wherever the parent species grow together; it is fertile, and introgression appears to take place. It usually has the brightly-coloured bark of {\b 2}, but at least some glandular-hairs on the young twigs.
